You cant really do that in ES6.You&#x27;d have to use a co-routine framework (and a &quot;thunkifier&quot;) and a generator that would yield some stuff.<p>something like<p><pre><code>   co(function *(){
      for(i in uids){
        users[i] = yield thunkify(load_users)(uids[i]);
      }
   });
</code></pre>
While generators are useful, they dont make async code look like sync code.
